ratings.comment: She is the most inconsiderate professor I've ever had. Just plain rude. I got an A in her class, but not without my life being miserable last semester because of it. I didn't learn anything either. It was like she is a teacher only to feel control over other people's' lives. I wouldn't recommend her. Stay as far away as you possibly can.

An awesome TA. Challenging if you're not into the class or the major. But she's willing to help and puts forth a great effort. Lessons are clear and practical. One of my favorite TA's in the department.

Michelle is a fantastic TA. Loved her 226. Consistently got B's on her tests but very high A's on papers. Just five papers - short and easy prompts. Her class will be easy for you if you love Spanish. If not, it'll challenge you, but I think it's definitely worth it. Learned a lot and really developed my skills.
Great TA, she is always prepared and knows what she's talking about.  She really cares about her students and my class had a lot of fun with her.  Not a difficult class if you put any effort in.
Completely unbearable.  I would rank her as on of the bottom 5 instructors I have had at UW.  This is because she would give me attitude for no reason whatsoever if I asked her anything.

Michelle is a great TA. She was always enthusiastic and swtiched things up in class. 100% improvement from my last spanish class. Class was fun and interactive and she is always willing to explain things to you. Definitely hope to have her again next semester!

I had her for spanish 204, and I loved her. I hope I get her for 226. She is really easy to understand, and she always makes sure you understand. If you are struggling, go in for office hours. She is really helpful!
She was great! Always willing to help, super funny, always mixing things up, and really cares... I don't know where these other comments are coming from.. My whole class loved her!

Are you kidding me? She was awesome! Everything was very clear, she was never in a bad mood, she has a great sense of humor, and the tests were very fair and fairly graded. I was so surprised to see these comments! She was the best T.A. I had!
It was the worse class I could have taken for my FIRST SEMESTER EVER in college.
Didn't really like her at all. Thought she was rude.
Warning: TA on power trip. Michelle is very rude, and writes really unfair tests.
